result.execSummary:
The defendant Jayden D. Prindiville was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of a Firearm by a Felon [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child (No Harm and Child < 6 Yrs or Disability) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Order (on Joint Stipulation Re: Sentence Credit)
It is hereby ordered that:
1. The clerk of court shall file an Amended Judgment of Conviction in 21CF1319 to reflect 16 days of credit.
2. The clerk of court shall file an Amended Judgment of Conviction in 22CF520 to reflect 62 days of credit.
Proposed Order (on Joint Stipulation Re: Sentence Credit)
Joint Stipulation Re: Sentence Credit
Reminder Notice indicating amount due mailed to defendant.

Cases called at 11:50 AM: 21CF1319, 22CF520, 21CT244, 21CT249.  Hearing held via Zoom and in person.
Defendant Jayden D. Prindiville appeared by video, in custody from Chippewa County Jail.  Attorney Melissa M. Petersen in court for Jayden D. Prindiville.  Attorney Monica A Fallon in court for State of Wisconsin. 
State in compliance with victim notification requirements. Counsel state sentencing recommendations.  Defendant waives his right to personal appearance.
21CF1319: Court imposes but stays 1 and 1/2 Years of Initial Confinement and 2 Years of Extended Supervision and places the Defendant on 3 Years of Probation. 
22CF520 (Count 1): Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 5 Years of Probation. 
22CF520 (Count 5): Court imposes but stays 3 Years of Initial Confinement and 3 Years of Extended Supervision and places the Defendant on 4 Years of Probation.
All sentences are concurrent to one another. 
Conditions of Probation:
No contact with Co-Defendant A.B-H. unless and until approved by the agent. No contact with B.P. unless and until approved by the agent.
No acts or threats of violence against anyone. Write down the following and read to self no less than 3 times a day: " I take personal responsibility for my actions."
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Court Costs/surcharges. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Defendant is granted 62 days of credit in 22CF520 and 1 day of credit in 21CF1319.
Sentencing hearing on October 31, 2022 at 11:30 am.

10am Cases called: 22CF520, 21CF1319, 21CT244 & 21CT249. Defendant Jayden D. Prindiville in court.  Attorney Melissa M. Petersen in court for Jayden D. Prindiville.  Attorney Andrew Gunderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives reading of Information in the felony cases and enters Not Guilty pleas. There is an joint agreement that involves a imposed and stayed prison sentence. 

Defendant enters a no contest plea to:
Count 1 in 21CF1319: Possession of Methamphetamine. 
Count 1 in 22CF520: Possession of a Firearm by a Felon by a Repeater
Count 5 in 22CF520: Neglecting a Child as a Repeater

Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Court accepts the plea and finds the defendant guilty. Anything else including 21CT244 & 21CT249 and any citations are ordered dismissed and read in.  Parties recites details the agreement; Court does not agree with recommendation. 

Sentencing Hearing: 10/31/22 at 11:30am Bond continues.
